WEBVTT

00:03.385 --> 00:06.598
So, honey, Ibiza can only
take us at 6:30 tonight.

00:06.681 --> 00:09.016
Great. I will
meet you at Ibiza.

00:09.099 --> 00:11.269
It's pronounced “Ibitha,”
not Ibiza.

00:11.352 --> 00:13.020
Oh! Thanks, honey.

00:13.103 --> 00:16.356
That reminds me. This weekend I want
to see that baby panda at the thoo.

00:16.440 --> 00:17.774
[ Both Laughing ]

00:17.858 --> 00:20.193
Yeah. I'm the idiot.

00:20.277 --> 00:23.323
This year, for Valentine's Day, we're
gonna have a nice, quiet dinner at Ibiza.

00:23.405 --> 00:25.908
Last year, we, um-

00:25.992 --> 00:28.118
we overreached a little.

00:28.201 --> 00:30.913
We created sexy alter egos,
Clive and Juliana,

00:30.997 --> 00:32.456
met in the hotel bar.

00:32.540 --> 00:34.751
This one lost her panties
in the lobby, in front of her dad-

00:34.876 --> 00:36.336
Phil. [ Chuckles ]
which was a little-

00:36.419 --> 00:39.004
It was hard.
It was hard for her.

00:39.129 --> 00:41.632
You know I can't stand it when
you use that word. Panties?

00:41.715 --> 00:43.925
Ye- That- Yes. That word.

00:44.010 --> 00:46.721
Sorry. She lost her underpanties.

00:50.308 --> 00:53.477
- So?
- So?

00:53.560 --> 00:55.605
Well? Huh? So?

00:55.687 --> 00:58.440
- What's happening?
- Flowers.

00:58.523 --> 01:00.150
Is someone pointing
a gun at you?

01:00.233 --> 01:02.819
For goodness' sake.
Did you get the flowers Lily and I sent you?

01:02.904 --> 01:06.115
Aw, that's so sweet. No.
No, I didn't get anything.

01:06.198 --> 01:07.824
Really.

01:07.909 --> 01:09.868
Did you check with that assistant of yours?

01:09.951 --> 01:11.621
Broderick?

01:11.704 --> 01:13.330
[ Phone Rings]

01:14.415 --> 01:16.083
Uh, did you get any flowers today?

01:16.166 --> 01:18.377
No. Sadly, I'm without
a valentine this year.

01:18.460 --> 01:21.505
No. For Mitchell.
The flowers are for Mitchell!

01:21.588 --> 01:24.258
Oh, that's right. Oops.

01:24.341 --> 01:27.844
- Mitchell's assistant has a huge crush on him.
- He does not!

01:27.928 --> 01:30.639
I think the only prudent thing
to do is say, “You're fired.”

01:30.722 --> 01:33.684
Don't be jealous.
He just looks up to me.

01:33.767 --> 01:36.187
The thing about Mitchell
is he can be naive.

01:36.270 --> 01:39.856
He is completely unaware of
how absolutely adorable he is.

01:39.940 --> 01:43.443
Okay. Well, thank you, but I am aware
when someone has a crush on me,

01:43.528 --> 01:46.781
and he does not have
a crush on me.

01:46.864 --> 01:48.449
[ Mouthing Words]

01:50.117 --> 01:52.035
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:52.120 --> 01:54.080
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:54.163 --> 01:56.165
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:56.248 --> 01:58.083
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:58.166 --> 01:59.168
♪ Hey ♪♪

02:01.629 --> 02:04.715
I was a little concerned when they said
they could only take us at 6:30, but-

02:04.840 --> 02:08.175
I know. This house is on fire, right?
Mm-hmm.

02:08.258 --> 02:10.470
Now, this is how you do V-Day.

02:10.554 --> 02:14.014
Except most of these people
could have been here on V-E Day.

02:14.140 --> 02:17.853
But it's classy, which we deserve.
Yes, we do.

02:17.936 --> 02:21.105
What were we thinking last year,
acting like a couple of teenagers?

02:21.188 --> 02:23.108
I know. Oh.

02:23.191 --> 02:26.736
Hey, we've had our crazy
Valentine's Days. We tore it up.

02:26.861 --> 02:29.740
But you gotta know when to
let that stuff go. Yeah.

02:29.823 --> 02:31.157
All those kids out there...

02:31.240 --> 02:32.950
are just lookin' for something
that we've already got.

02:33.033 --> 02:34.161
Yeah.

02:34.286 --> 02:35.912
I love you.
I love you too.

02:35.995 --> 02:37.705
[ Crash ]
Oh, my gosh!

02:37.830 --> 02:39.206
Wow! Okay. I'm sorry.
Are you all right?

02:39.331 --> 02:41.168
Are you okay? Are you all right?
I'm good. We're good.

02:41.293 --> 02:44.670
It's my first day in one of these things.
Hey, let me help you out.

02:44.795 --> 02:47.549
How 'bout I park it over there
for you, okay? Thank you.

02:47.632 --> 02:49.425
Here's your valet ticket.
[ Chuckling ]

02:49.509 --> 02:51.552
I'm kidding actually.
That's my valet ticket.

02:53.180 --> 02:55.848
All right. Let's see.

02:55.932 --> 02:57.933
Lefty loosey.
Righty tighty.

02:58.018 --> 02:59.478
Hey.
Wow.

02:59.561 --> 03:02.188
All right. Hey!

03:02.271 --> 03:04.441
This is fun, Claire.
You gotta try this.

03:04.524 --> 03:05.942
Phil.

03:06.067 --> 03:07.610
He's a natural.
Thank you.

03:07.693 --> 03:10.530
[ Motor Whirring ]

03:10.614 --> 03:13.282
[ Claire ] I know Phil and I are
gonna grow old together some day.

03:13.365 --> 03:14.992
This thing needs mirrors.

03:15.075 --> 03:18.204
But today is not that day.

03:19.538 --> 03:23.043
[Cell Phone Ringing]

03:25.419 --> 03:27.798
[ Beeps ]
Hello.

03:27.881 --> 03:29.966
Hello. May I speak to Clive?

03:30.091 --> 03:32.843
I'm sorry. I think you have the wrong number.
Bye-bye. No, uh-

03:34.221 --> 03:36.764
I got disconnected.
Would you mind redialing?

03:38.015 --> 03:39.683
[ Rings]

03:39.768 --> 03:41.937
[Line Ringing]

03:42.019 --> 03:43.729
Hello.

03:43.813 --> 03:46.191
Hello, Clive. This is Juliana.

03:46.274 --> 03:48.317
Look, lady.
Please stop calling me. This is-

03:48.401 --> 03:50.486
No,no,no,no. No, Phil, Phil, Phil.
Don't hang up.

03:50.569 --> 03:52.948
Claire?
No, no, no. Not Claire.

03:53.031 --> 03:55.283
Juliana.

03:55.366 --> 03:57.284
And you're Clive Bixby.
Remember?

03:57.369 --> 03:59.120
We met at the hotel bar last year.

03:59.204 --> 04:00.705
Oh!

04:02.581 --> 04:04.042
Oh.

04:04.125 --> 04:07.461
Now, make up some lie,
ditch that wife of yours,

04:07.545 --> 04:09.339
and meet me at our hotel
in 30 minutes.

04:09.421 --> 04:10.924
You think you can manage that?

04:11.007 --> 04:14.845
Baby doll, I've been lying
to my wife for 16 years.

04:14.927 --> 04:17.055
Okay. See ya.

04:18.848 --> 04:19.975
[Beeps]

04:20.809 --> 04:22.560
So, champagne?

04:22.644 --> 04:25.605
Um, actually, Claire,
somethings come up,

04:25.689 --> 04:27.690
so... gotta go.

04:27.774 --> 04:31.026
You're not ditching me here on Valentine's Day.
Screw that. Sit.

04:31.110 --> 04:33.905
But- Wh- Oh, okay.

04:33.988 --> 04:36.408
We'll- We'll Stay.

04:36.533 --> 04:38.410
Phil.
Oh, that's part of it?

04:38.492 --> 04:40.370
[ Chuckles ]
So hot.

04:40.452 --> 04:42.497
Claire. I'm leaving.
Deal with it.

04:42.622 --> 04:45.416
[Woman Gasps ]
[Clattering ]

04:45.500 --> 04:48.086
So no one walks any more!

04:52.798 --> 04:54.134
[ Chattering ]

04:54.216 --> 04:55.843
Should be just
a few more minutes.

04:55.968 --> 04:58.096
When is our reservation?
Here's the thing.

04:58.179 --> 05:00.389
Ay no. Not “the thing.”
I hate “the thing.”

05:00.473 --> 05:03.184
My secretary screwed up and
didn't get us one. Don't worry.

05:03.267 --> 05:04.603
I'll slip the guy
a few bucks.

05:04.685 --> 05:08.273
What kind of idiot messes up
two Valentine's in a row?

05:08.355 --> 05:09.858
Not this idiot.

05:09.940 --> 05:13.110
Two months ago I booked a private
chef, musicians, the works...

05:13.194 --> 05:15.404
for a romantic dinner at home.

05:15.488 --> 05:20.242
I just had to get the senorita out
of the house while they set up.

05:20.326 --> 05:23.120
This is 50 bucks.
Do not give us a table.

05:23.204 --> 05:24.663
What's the money for?

05:24.747 --> 05:27.834
You also must refuse my wife.
She's very persuasive.

05:29.043 --> 05:30.336
Just a couple
more minutes.

05:30.420 --> 05:33.339
So we don't get the table
at the fancy restaurant,

05:33.423 --> 05:35.091
which drives Gloria crazy.

05:35.175 --> 05:38.762
[ Imitating Gloria ] Jay, why you
no be no more romantic to me?

05:38.844 --> 05:41.514
[ Normal Voice]
We walk in the door and- bam!

05:41.598 --> 05:43.391
She looks like a big idiot.

05:45.517 --> 05:47.978
And isn't that what
Valentine's Day is all about?

05:49.647 --> 05:51.065
Jay, come here.
We're in.

05:51.190 --> 05:53.485
Huh? Your secretary didn't forget.
Look.

05:53.567 --> 05:56.320
Pritchett for two.

05:57.089 --> 06:00.163
Subtitles downloaded from Podnapisi.NET

06:02.493 --> 06:05.119
Just a reminder:
I need the television at 8:00.

06:05.203 --> 06:07.998
Jeremy and I have a phone date
to watch Love Actually.

06:09.290 --> 06:12.335
That's the lamest plan ever,
and I'm jealous.

06:12.419 --> 06:15.881
So my boyfriend, David, blows me off on
the most romantic night of the year-

06:15.965 --> 06:17.299
to study!

06:17.383 --> 06:18.926
This is the worst
Valentine's Day-

06:19.008 --> 06:21.136
Best Valentines Day ever!

06:21.220 --> 06:25.265
David stands up Haley, and old
boyfriend Dylan is out of the picture.

06:25.349 --> 06:28.893
I'm not saying I miss Dylan,
but at least he was romantic.

06:28.977 --> 06:31.604
David never sent me
a jar of his own tears.

06:31.688 --> 06:33.482
I'm playing the long game here.

06:33.564 --> 06:35.775
Like me today,
love me tomorrow.

06:35.859 --> 06:38.821
She's had the romantic.
She's had the intellectual.

06:38.904 --> 06:41.448
How 'bout all that
in one fine little brown package?

06:42.323 --> 06:44.284
[Sighs]
I've hit a new low.

06:44.367 --> 06:45.994
You can talk to me.

06:46.078 --> 06:47.537
And I'm lower.

06:47.621 --> 06:50.624
Just pickin' up some things.
I am not here.

06:50.708 --> 06:53.751
Name tags. Name tags.
Name tags.

06:53.835 --> 06:55.838
Come on! Bingo.

06:57.881 --> 06:59.340
I know what to do.

06:59.424 --> 07:01.051
Dylan's been
texting me again.

07:01.135 --> 07:04.054
I bet if David knew that, he'd
come running right over here.

07:04.138 --> 07:06.597
Wait. Before you start
playing these games,

07:06.681 --> 07:09.309
let me ask you
one simple question.

07:09.393 --> 07:10.893
Who is Haley Dunphy?

07:20.778 --> 07:23.323
Don't do it, Haley!
Stop following me.

07:23.448 --> 07:26.035
Let me just say my piece!
No!

07:28.412 --> 07:30.873
[ Sighs ]
Look.

07:30.955 --> 07:34.042
You can be the Haley who defines
herself as David's girlfriend...

07:34.126 --> 07:35.626
or Dylan's girlfriend.

07:35.710 --> 07:37.463
Or you can be
your own Haley.

07:37.545 --> 07:40.049
Maybe you haven't met her,
but I know her.

07:40.131 --> 07:41.717
She's an amazing person.

07:41.799 --> 07:44.720
So when you're ready,
I'd like to introduce you.

07:54.020 --> 07:56.023
[ Phone Rings]

07:56.106 --> 07:58.525
Cameron! Is there something
I can do you for?

07:58.609 --> 08:02.153
No. I just came by to pick up my man.
I'm taking him to Ibiza tonight.

08:02.237 --> 08:04.114
Oh, I've heard good things
about Ibiza.

08:04.198 --> 08:07.200
But I'm afraid he may have to meet you there.
He's in the middle of a meeting.

08:07.325 --> 08:10.662
- On Valentine's night?
- I didn't realize when I scheduled it. It's my fault.

08:10.746 --> 08:12.705
Gasp. I'm shocked.

08:12.789 --> 08:15.751
I could drop him off at the restaurant
as soon as they wrap it up.

08:15.833 --> 08:17.460
Oh. Aren't you a dear.

08:17.544 --> 08:19.838
[ Muttering ] I'd like to mount
your head in my trophy room.

08:20.963 --> 08:22.549
Cam!

08:23.508 --> 08:24.801
Wait.

08:26.011 --> 08:28.513
Have I upset you
in any way?

08:28.597 --> 08:30.599
Oh, please.
Let's not play this game.

08:30.681 --> 08:32.726
We both know
what's going on.

08:33.809 --> 08:35.602
Have I been that obvious?

08:35.687 --> 08:37.481
Uh, the flowers
that don't get delivered.

08:37.563 --> 08:39.440
The Valentine's Day plans
that get interrupted.

08:39.525 --> 08:43.153
Do I really need to spell it out for you?
Me, Mitchell- wedge.

08:45.322 --> 08:47.406
Don't hate me.

08:47.491 --> 08:51.953
It's just so hard to see someone else
have something you want and can't have.

08:52.036 --> 08:53.163
[ Sniffles ]

08:53.246 --> 08:55.999
Does Broderick
have a crush? Yes.

08:56.083 --> 08:59.086
On someone he frequently
sees at the office? Yes.

08:59.169 --> 09:00.670
Hi.

09:01.880 --> 09:03.924
Does that man
have red hair and a beard?

09:04.006 --> 09:06.217
No. But his boyfriend does.

09:07.678 --> 09:09.596
It's me.
The crush is on me.

09:09.679 --> 09:11.180
[ Elevator Bell Dings]

09:12.182 --> 09:13.891
This is you?

09:15.102 --> 09:17.395
Oh! Did I validate you?

09:17.478 --> 09:19.063
Oh, yes.

09:20.565 --> 09:23.526
♪♪ [ Piano: Romantic]

09:31.076 --> 09:32.578
Mmm.

09:35.581 --> 09:37.583
[ Exhales ]

09:43.881 --> 09:46.257
Appletini?
It was.

09:47.425 --> 09:49.011
[ Clears Throat]

09:49.093 --> 09:51.012
You're looking handsome
as ever, Clive.

09:51.096 --> 09:55.641
As are you, Juliana.
You look hot enough to cook a pizza on-

09:56.309 --> 09:57.394
in.

09:57.477 --> 09:59.855
I see the speaker business
is treating you well.

09:59.980 --> 10:02.274
I don't like to talk about money.
Oh.

10:02.399 --> 10:05.068
But I have exactly $10 million.
Hmm.

10:05.151 --> 10:07.154
Minus the cost
of your next drink.

10:07.237 --> 10:10.280
T- Two.
Just two appletinis, please.

10:10.364 --> 10:12.283
Thank you so much.

10:12.950 --> 10:14.534
Yeah.

10:14.619 --> 10:17.830
Why do I get the feeling
you're not really a salesman?

10:17.955 --> 10:20.207
Oh. Pretty and smart.
[ Chuckling ]

10:20.290 --> 10:22.335
Or should I say
“pretty smart”'?

10:22.418 --> 10:23.543
Mmm.

10:23.628 --> 10:26.172
I might do some high-risk
work for Uncle Sam...

10:26.255 --> 10:28.548
that takes me clear
around the country.

10:28.633 --> 10:32.803
Hmm. So you could say you're
a national man of mystery.

10:32.886 --> 10:34.554
Shh.

10:34.679 --> 10:37.225
Never did catch what you do.
Didn't you?

10:37.308 --> 10:38.768
Surprising, I know.

10:38.851 --> 10:42.896
I'm usually pretty good at catching
things from women in bars.

10:42.980 --> 10:47.610
Well, Clive, I am just a bored
housewife with a dark side...

10:47.692 --> 10:49.194
and an hour to kill.

10:50.154 --> 10:51.989
Is that what I think it is?

10:52.072 --> 10:53.573
It's not a gift card.

10:53.658 --> 10:56.117
Or maybe it is.

10:57.577 --> 10:59.413
I'll be upstairs, Clive.

10:59.496 --> 11:01.624
Don't take too long.

11:04.125 --> 11:05.628
I never do.

11:13.552 --> 11:15.053
Mercy.

11:19.058 --> 11:21.894
Jay, relax. I'm sorry.
The place is a dump.

11:22.019 --> 11:24.020
It's beautiful.
Nothing good on the menu.

11:24.105 --> 11:26.649
You see the hands on our waiter?
Looks like he's been birthing hogs.

11:26.774 --> 11:29.485
Let's just get out of here.
I don't know what's wrong with you tonight.

11:29.567 --> 11:32.071
But I'm hungry. I look fantastic.
We're staying.

11:32.154 --> 11:36.951
Five-course dinner waiting at home,
and she's strapping on the feed bag at Ibiza.

11:37.034 --> 11:39.287
But then an angel from heaven
saved the night.

11:39.370 --> 11:42.914
You took our reservation.
“Pritchett for two” is us.

11:42.999 --> 11:45.208
Come on. Let's go. Move your bottom.
Come on, come on!

11:45.293 --> 11:47.419
A big gay angel.

11:50.047 --> 11:51.548
[ Lock Beeps ]

11:55.760 --> 11:57.263
[ Door Closes ]

12:02.226 --> 12:03.644
[Beeps]

12:03.727 --> 12:07.481
[Cell Phone Ringing]

12:07.564 --> 12:08.982
[Beeps]

12:09.066 --> 12:11.652
Hello.
Hello, Clive.

12:11.736 --> 12:13.236
How close are you?

12:13.321 --> 12:15.822
I am right
outside your door.

12:15.905 --> 12:17.908
Oh! Are you ready?

12:17.991 --> 12:19.492
Oh, I'm ready.

12:19.577 --> 12:22.538
I don't think you are, 'cause
I can still hear your pants.

12:22.620 --> 12:25.249
Well, maybe I should
just shut them up.

12:25.332 --> 12:29.044
[Chuckling ]
I'll be out in a minute.

12:29.128 --> 12:32.630
So Will I.

12:58.865 --> 13:01.452
[ Rings]

13:02.370 --> 13:03.370
[Beeps]

13:03.453 --> 13:04.913
Juliana.

13:04.996 --> 13:07.415
Clive. Where are you?

13:07.500 --> 13:09.710
You have to come find me.

13:09.793 --> 13:12.295
Oh.
[ Laughing]

13:12.380 --> 13:14.215
Hello.

13:14.298 --> 13:15.799
Um-

13:18.093 --> 13:19.886
I give up.
Where are you?

13:19.970 --> 13:21.806
I'm right here on the bed.

13:23.014 --> 13:25.518
- Phil, what room are you in?
- Who's this “Phil”'?

13:25.601 --> 13:27.061
Seriously,
what room are you in?

13:27.144 --> 13:29.105
I'm in 702.

13:29.187 --> 13:31.399
I'm in 226.
What?

13:31.524 --> 13:33.942
Well, whose room is this then?
[ Lock Beeps ]

13:37.487 --> 13:38.322
[ Gasps ]

13:39.490 --> 13:40.950
There's been a tiny mistake.

13:41.033 --> 13:42.076
[ Cork Pops ]

13:47.498 --> 13:49.375
By the way, I need
to apologize to you.

13:49.457 --> 13:51.876
I'm sorry I got so silly with all
that Broderick stuff earlier.

13:51.961 --> 13:54.797
No. Please do not
worry about it.

13:54.922 --> 13:58.216
Cam. I like it when you get a
little jealous. Cut it out.

13:58.299 --> 14:01.095
As long as we can agree
he does not have a crush on me.

14:01.178 --> 14:02.471
Absolutely.

14:02.554 --> 14:04.889
So, to us.
To us.

14:05.933 --> 14:08.018
He does not have a crush on you.
No.

14:08.852 --> 14:10.437
Nope.

14:10.520 --> 14:12.772
Why do I feel like
you're hinting at something?

14:12.855 --> 14:16.484
Mitchell, we have talked long
enough about Broderick's crush.

14:16.567 --> 14:19.070
Which he does not have.
On you.

14:19.195 --> 14:21.239
Oh, my God. What?
Okay, fine.

14:21.321 --> 14:24.451
Since you won't let it go,
your assistant is hot for me.

14:24.533 --> 14:26.702
That's why he's been
playing the saboteur.

14:26.786 --> 14:30.373
- And you're sure it's not because he wants me?
- You just said he didn't.

14:30.456 --> 14:32.459
- I was protecting your feelings.
- He hugged me in the elevator.

14:32.542 --> 14:35.128
Well, pick out china and move to Vermont.

14:35.211 --> 14:37.839
He said it kills him to see someone
else have something he wants.

14:37.922 --> 14:40.090
Yes, yes. You're the someone,
and I'm the something.

14:40.174 --> 14:41.967
Okay. All right. Call him.

14:42.092 --> 14:44.178
Call him?
Call him.

14:44.262 --> 14:45.763
Why don't we go to his house,

14:45.846 --> 14:48.224
stand on opposite sides of the room
and see which one he runs to?

14:48.307 --> 14:49.808
You get the check.
I'll get the car.

14:49.893 --> 14:52.604
We are not going over there.
And we're not calling him.

14:52.686 --> 14:55.398
Cam. Who cares which one of us
he has a crush on?

14:55.481 --> 14:59.652
The important thing is,
I have a crush on you.

14:59.735 --> 15:02.571
And I wouldn't blame Broderick
if he did too.

15:02.654 --> 15:04.657
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

15:04.740 --> 15:06.701
That's so sweet. I-

15:06.783 --> 15:08.952
I wouldn't blame him if he
had a crush on you either.

15:09.037 --> 15:11.371
Aw. Good.

15:13.249 --> 15:15.502
“Good” what?
Just “good.”

15:15.585 --> 15:17.586
“Good,” meaning
we're done with this,

15:17.669 --> 15:20.005
or “Good,” meaning you still think
he has a crush on you?

15:20.089 --> 15:21.883
Oh, Cam!

15:23.634 --> 15:25.637
The second one.
I'm getting the car.

15:31.350 --> 15:33.393
Would you please
just come in the house?

15:33.478 --> 15:36.563
You had the whole year to plan,
but you don't make an effort.

15:36.648 --> 15:40.276
I am the second wife, Jay.
Why do you treat me like I'm the first?

15:40.360 --> 15:42.486
Talk about it inside.
Where you going?

15:42.570 --> 15:44.531
I'm gonna take a ride.
I need to cool down.

15:44.656 --> 15:48.116
Just come in the house. I promise you'll feel better.
I don't want to go in there.

15:48.243 --> 15:50.577
You're gonna like it better inside.
Don't hold me back!

15:50.662 --> 15:52.997
I'm sorry about this, honey.
I'm sorry.

15:53.081 --> 15:55.124
Jay, what are you doing?
Are you crazy?

15:55.207 --> 15:57.918
¡Ay! ¡Se me va a romper
la media, oye!

15:58.001 --> 16:00.421
What are you doing?
Have you lost your mind?

16:00.504 --> 16:02.673
No. But you're about to.

16:02.757 --> 16:05.259
Happy Valentine's Day!

16:09.263 --> 16:11.099
What the hell?

16:12.767 --> 16:14.018
Gloria!

16:14.978 --> 16:17.437
- Honey.
- I'm going for a drive.

16:17.522 --> 16:20.233
I had a whole private dinner planned.
I don't know what happened.

16:20.316 --> 16:21.901
But I do.
[ Garage Door Opens]

16:21.985 --> 16:23.820
I know exactly
what happened!

16:23.903 --> 16:25.404
No, you don't. I-

16:25.488 --> 16:27.322
♪♪ [Violin]

16:30.201 --> 16:31.952
what the hell?

16:32.036 --> 16:33.245
I win!

16:33.329 --> 16:36.416
I see you sneaking around,
trying to trick me.

16:36.499 --> 16:41.045
So when I figure it out, I move the
party over here and I trick you!

16:41.170 --> 16:43.255
I win!
What do you mean, you win?

16:43.339 --> 16:45.549
I know you think I think
you're not romantic,

16:45.633 --> 16:48.385
but I think you think
I'm not smarter than you.

16:48.469 --> 16:52.389
So now we know. You are romantic,
and I'm smarter than you.

16:52.472 --> 16:55.268
And I bought you
a motorcycle.

16:55.350 --> 16:57.061
[ Jay ]
My God. It's fantastic!

16:57.144 --> 16:58.605
I win again!

16:58.687 --> 17:02.483
Honey, I love all this, but you
can't win Valentine's Day.

17:02.566 --> 17:06.944
I mean, you defeat the whole idea
if you make it into some silly competition.

17:07.029 --> 17:09.114
Shut up. I win.

17:09.198 --> 17:11.034
♪♪ [Violin Continues]

17:12.367 --> 17:13.744
[ Keys Rattling ]
Let's go.

17:13.869 --> 17:15.579
So we're doing this?
Oh, we're doing this.

17:15.704 --> 17:17.957
Oh, it's gonna be me.
I'm already embarrassed for you.

17:18.040 --> 17:19.290
All right.
[ Phone Beeps ]

17:19.415 --> 17:21.419
Oh, wait.
What?

17:21.544 --> 17:23.880
Oh, it's a text from Broderick.
Read it.

17:25.047 --> 17:27.467
“Mitchell, by now
I'm sure Cameron has told you...

17:27.592 --> 17:29.469
What happened in the elevator.”
Mm-hmm.

17:29.551 --> 17:34.140
“While I meant every word I said,
I realize how unprofessional I was.

17:34.222 --> 17:36.224
Please accept my resignation.

17:36.308 --> 17:38.435
What you have with Cam
is very special,

17:38.518 --> 17:41.814
and I would never forgive myself
if I came between you.

17:41.897 --> 17:44.232
Treasure each other.
Sincerely, Broderick.”

17:46.027 --> 17:48.654
Wow. Oh, Cam.
What are we doing here?

17:48.738 --> 17:50.530
I don't know.

17:50.614 --> 17:53.159
Maybe if some assistant's crush
is so important to us,

17:53.241 --> 17:57.497
it means we should appreciate
each other a little bit more.

17:57.579 --> 18:00.415
Well, I can't think of a better
time to start. Come here.

18:00.499 --> 18:02.210
Mmm.
Ahhh.

18:02.293 --> 18:06.130
The great thing about that text is we don't
have to know which one of us he wanted.

18:06.213 --> 18:09.424
I know.

18:15.221 --> 18:17.056
What are you doing?

18:17.140 --> 18:20.686
Valentine's Day
isn't over yet, Juliana.

18:20.768 --> 18:23.438
Sweetie, let's not push it.
You almost got arrested tonight.

18:23.521 --> 18:26.274
That's how it's gonna be?
You're just givin' up on us?

18:26.357 --> 18:28.026
I am not giving up on us.

18:28.110 --> 18:31.196
I'm giving up
on Clive and Juliana.

18:31.278 --> 18:33.280
Wait. Wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait.

18:33.364 --> 18:35.741
I know a couple people who could
possibly save this night.

18:35.866 --> 18:37.494
Hmm. Maybe you've heard of 'em.

18:37.576 --> 18:41.539
Two American kids doing
the best that they can.

18:41.623 --> 18:43.458
Phil and Claire Dunphy.

18:43.542 --> 18:46.961
I am not going back to that hotel tonight,
and I'm pretty sure you're not allowed to.

18:47.045 --> 18:49.046
Don't need to.
Phil and Claire have a bedroom,

18:49.131 --> 18:52.383
which they can turn into a
hotel whenever they want.

18:52.508 --> 18:55.886
But the kids. They're not
expecting us home this early.

18:56.887 --> 18:58.640
So,

18:58.723 --> 19:00.683
you up for
a little adventure,

19:02.352 --> 19:03.979
Claire?

19:04.062 --> 19:06.230
Do you think
you can handle it,

19:07.190 --> 19:08.190
Phil?

19:10.152 --> 19:11.152
[ Phil Chuckles]

19:11.236 --> 19:12.821
[Claire] Shh. Shh. Sorry.

19:12.903 --> 19:15.156
“I can't be the girl
you want me to be, David.

19:15.239 --> 19:17.616
I can only be me.
Good-bye.

19:17.700 --> 19:19.035
Haley.”

19:19.119 --> 19:20.786
Send it.

19:20.911 --> 19:23.414
I don't know.
Here. I'll help you.

19:23.498 --> 19:25.459
No,no,no,no,
no,no,no,no!

19:25.542 --> 19:27.043
[ Whooshing Sound]

19:28.085 --> 19:29.880
Wow.

19:30.005 --> 19:33.216
That feels really good.
Because you're free.

19:33.299 --> 19:36.678
And really scary.
I haven't been single since I was nine.

19:36.761 --> 19:38.764
That's why you need
to take your time now.

19:38.846 --> 19:41.682
Really get to know yourself
before you make any decisions.

19:41.767 --> 19:43.392
Five, six years maybe.

19:43.477 --> 19:45.770
Years? I have to call David.

19:45.854 --> 19:48.481
The boy who tossed you aside
on Valentine's Day?

19:48.565 --> 19:49.607
No.

19:49.690 --> 19:51.276
You deserve better, Haley.

19:51.358 --> 19:53.444
A dreamer, a poet.

19:53.527 --> 19:57.615
Wait for him.
He may be closer than you think.

19:57.699 --> 19:59.159
[ Faint]
♪ I'm the bread without your butter ♪

19:59.284 --> 20:01.411
Do you hear music?
Yes.

20:01.495 --> 20:03.078
And the fact
that you hear it too-

20:03.162 --> 20:04.122
Is that Dylan?

20:04.206 --> 20:05.790
♪ Who could make me
feel this fine ♪

20:05.873 --> 20:07.374
Oh, my God!

20:07.459 --> 20:13.757
♪ So here's my broken valentine ♪

20:14.508 --> 20:17.469
♪ Imagine me naked ♪

20:17.552 --> 20:20.555
♪ I imagine you nude ♪

20:20.639 --> 20:23.517
Am I a bad enough parent
to ignore that?

20:23.600 --> 20:25.477
You are.

20:25.559 --> 20:27.312
You're really bad.

20:29.689 --> 20:34.527
♪ Without my best friend ♪

20:34.611 --> 20:36.112
You know, the old Haley
would have-

20:36.196 --> 20:37.322
I love you, baby!

20:37.404 --> 20:39.240
Haley!
Oh!

20:39.324 --> 20:42.160
♪♪ [Continues]

20:42.244 --> 20:44.371
¡Salud, Jay!

20:47.164 --> 20:49.500
Mmm.
Oh-oh! OW!

20:49.584 --> 20:50.960
Phil?
There's my back.

20:54.756 --> 20:56.508
Oh. Oh. No. Keep the change.

20:56.591 --> 20:58.008
Oh, thanks.

20:58.093 --> 21:00.178
Did you put an extra tiramisu
in here?

21:00.303 --> 21:02.180
Maybe.
Ryan! Again?

21:02.264 --> 21:04.056
I just like coming here.

21:04.181 --> 21:06.642
I tell you, if you were
single- [ Both ] Oh!

21:08.436 --> 21:10.104
[ Chuckles ]

21:16.902 --> 21:19.238
[Chuckling]

21:20.323 --> 21:21.825
[ Both ]
Ryan!

21:28.873 --> 21:29.874
English - US - PSDH
